title: Easton's Nate Moser is Week 6 EPC defensive MVP
text:
Nate Moser , Easton Nate Moser (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) 
Just a week after Whitehall scored 28 points and gained 400 yards of offense against Parkland, Moser helped make sure those numbers shrunk when the Zephyrs played the Red Rovers. 
The senior cornerback intercepted a pass and returned it 42 yards for a touchdown in Easton's 45-0 win . Moser added seven tackles while limiting Whitehall to 69 total yards of offense and just 29 yards through the air.
